WEBVTT

00:00:04.755 --> 00:00:10.177
Is the destiny of mankind controlled
by some transcendental entity or Law?

00:00:10.928 --> 00:00:13.806
Is it like the hand of
God hovering above?

00:00:15.057 --> 00:00:16.767
At least it is true...

00:00:17.226 --> 00:00:20.896
...that man has no
control, even over his own will.

00:00:26.402 --> 00:00:27.653
Not my choice...

00:00:28.654 --> 00:00:29.780
I was not...

00:00:31.991 --> 00:00:34.326
I was not born to
be a woman by choice!

00:00:36.162 --> 00:00:41.709
I cannot forget the fact that your
selfishness exposed Griffith to lethal danger!

00:00:42.293 --> 00:00:45.212
I don't care if you drop
dead somewhere in battle!

00:00:45.337 --> 00:00:50.593
But, I will never forgive you if
you ruin the Hawks, Griffith's dream!

00:00:52.178 --> 00:00:56.348
And I can't forgive you for
making Griffith change like he has...

00:01:02.438 --> 00:01:03.355
Why?

00:01:05.649 --> 00:01:08.069
Why did he choose you?

00:01:08.778 --> 00:01:09.904
Why you?

00:01:11.000 --> 00:01:17.074
Support us and become VIP member 
to remove all ads from www.OpenSubtitles.org

00:01:30.716 --> 00:01:32.718
<i>Feel no shame about shape.</i>

00:01:32.843 --> 00:01:34.595
<i>Weather changes the phrase.</i>

00:01:34.845 --> 00:01:38.349
<i>Even mother will
show you another way.</i>

00:01:38.599 --> 00:01:40.810
<i>So, put your glasses on.</i>

00:01:40.935 --> 00:01:42.853
<i>Nothing will be wrong.</i>

00:01:42.978 --> 00:01:45.106
<i>There's no blame, there's no fame.</i>

00:01:45.231 --> 00:01:46.941
<i>It's up to you.</i>

00:01:47.108 --> 00:01:50.569
<i>The first words should be found.</i>

00:01:51.237 --> 00:01:54.115
<i>Whatever holds you back.</i>

00:01:54.990 --> 00:01:55.574
<i>I...</i>

00:01:55.991 --> 00:01:56.700
<i>... can...</i>

00:01:56.826 --> 00:01:58.869
<i>I can get it off.</i>

00:01:58.994 --> 00:01:59.870
<i>Tell me what...</i>

00:02:00.121 --> 00:02:00.871
<i>Tell me what...</i>

00:02:00.996 --> 00:02:02.706
<i>Tell me what you want.</i>

00:02:02.873 --> 00:02:03.833
<i>I don't know why...</i>

00:02:03.999 --> 00:02:04.750
<i>I don't know why...</i>

00:02:04.959 --> 00:02:06.752
<i>I don't know why you are afraid.</i>

00:02:07.002 --> 00:02:07.878
<i>Tell me what...</i>

00:02:08.087 --> 00:02:08.879
<i>Tell me what...</i>

00:02:09.130 --> 00:02:10.548
<i>Tell me what you'd say.</i>

00:02:10.881 --> 00:02:11.882
<i>I don't know why...</i>

00:02:12.049 --> 00:02:13.008
<i>I don't know why...</i>

00:02:13.134 --> 00:02:13.801
<i>Too late...</i>

00:02:13.926 --> 00:02:15.427
<i>It's too late.</i>

00:02:20.641 --> 00:02:24.645
Prepared for Death

00:03:32.630 --> 00:03:33.714
What's the matter?

00:03:34.006 --> 00:03:34.882
Are you giving up?

00:03:38.636 --> 00:03:42.514
Oh brother, a woman
can be such a nuisance.

00:03:43.641 --> 00:03:47.519
A woman has no strength and is
liable to go into a frenzy over nothing.

00:03:47.895 --> 00:03:49.605
Not only that, but
you're on your period.

00:03:50.731 --> 00:03:54.026
At any rate, women
just aren't cut out for war.

00:03:54.652 --> 00:03:56.737
You know nothing about women!

00:03:56.862 --> 00:03:59.031
Of course not, I'm a
man, so how could I know?

00:04:00.366 --> 00:04:04.119
What I do know is that
we don't have the time...

00:04:04.286 --> 00:04:07.665
...to be stranded here by your
woman's problem any longer.

00:04:08.540 --> 00:04:12.503
The enemy doesn't care about your
condition, or if you are a woman or not.

00:04:13.170 --> 00:04:16.340
On second thought, could they
be happy that you're a woman?

00:04:25.975 --> 00:04:26.850
Let's move!

00:05:22.031 --> 00:05:22.948
What the hell?

00:05:54.229 --> 00:05:57.691
Hey, is this a breeding
ground for swarms of mosquitos?

00:06:00.069 --> 00:06:01.487
I found you.

00:06:04.740 --> 00:06:07.743
I am glad you are alive, kid!

00:06:08.869 --> 00:06:11.497
Hey old man, you're
looking pretty good yourself.

00:06:11.622 --> 00:06:12.247
Shut up!

00:06:13.123 --> 00:06:18.087
Even though it was a fluke, a little
bastard like you caused me some real trouble.

00:06:18.253 --> 00:06:22.216
I, a proud knight of Chuder, could not
bear to die without rectifying such a problem!

00:06:22.466 --> 00:06:23.467
Oh, really?

00:06:23.842 --> 00:06:26.011
I'm not going to let you die easily.

00:06:26.136 --> 00:06:30.641
I will haul you off as a captive
and expose you to hell on earth.

00:06:30.849 --> 00:06:34.353
You'll enjoy a secret torture technique,
the hundred year <i>Monzetsu Goroshi</i>...

00:06:34.478 --> 00:06:37.523
...that has been passed down through
the Coborlwitz family for 200 years!

00:06:37.731 --> 00:06:39.900
You're the type who holds a grudge.

00:06:40.275 --> 00:06:42.653
It's fine if you
surrender without protest!

00:06:42.736 --> 00:06:43.987
But if you want to cross us...

00:06:43.987 --> 00:06:46.865
...we'll chop off your arms along
with any other body parts we like!

00:06:47.491 --> 00:06:49.410
All I need is for you to be alive.

00:06:49.910 --> 00:06:54.623
As for the woman, we will make her
a plaything for my soldiers right here!

00:06:55.416 --> 00:06:57.918
I have to suggest
that you don't try that.

00:06:59.670 --> 00:07:01.422
She is a truly scary woman.

00:07:02.172 --> 00:07:03.799
She'll rip you to shreds.

00:07:06.885 --> 00:07:08.762
How dare you joke around with me!

00:07:09.138 --> 00:07:10.305
Beat them down!

00:07:48.677 --> 00:07:51.722
I don't need your help anymore!

00:07:52.723 --> 00:07:53.682
Great!

00:07:53.932 --> 00:07:54.850
Damn!

00:07:54.975 --> 00:07:56.477
They are only two of them!

00:07:56.685 --> 00:07:57.352
Don't hesitate!

00:07:57.936 --> 00:07:59.938
Overwhelm them in a single charge!

00:08:55.327 --> 00:08:57.579
They are
incompetents, every one of them.

00:08:58.288 --> 00:08:59.081
Samson!

00:08:59.706 --> 00:09:01.083
Samson!

00:09:01.458 --> 00:09:04.086
Here, Big Brother!

00:09:16.974 --> 00:09:20.852
Assistant commander of the Blue
Whale Super Strong Heavy Assault Knights...

00:09:20.978 --> 00:09:21.937
Samson!

00:09:24.439 --> 00:09:27.818
He is my younger brother and the
second strongest warrior in my entire unit!

00:09:27.985 --> 00:09:32.364
Additionally, Samson's armor is three
times as thick as anyone elses'!

00:09:32.614 --> 00:09:35.242
Even if he's buried under an avalanche,
he would be absolutely indestructible!

00:09:38.829 --> 00:09:44.376
On top of all that, his iron ball can
crush a buffalo's head flat in a single blow!

00:09:44.751 --> 00:09:48.213
If a man gets hit squarely by it, there
will be nothing left but a piece of flesh!

00:09:49.131 --> 00:09:50.841
Now, I give you no quarter!

00:09:51.383 --> 00:09:52.759
Have them experience firsthand...

00:09:52.884 --> 00:09:54.761
...the esteemed techniques
of the Coborlwitz family!

00:10:01.518 --> 00:10:03.770
A sword would be smashed if it
tried to block his attacks directly.

00:10:08.150 --> 00:10:09.151
What should we do?

00:10:26.001 --> 00:10:27.252
He knocked it back?

00:10:35.052 --> 00:10:36.678
I can't believe it...

00:10:37.429 --> 00:10:40.432
He's beating back every
blow from Samson's iron ball...

00:10:43.685 --> 00:10:44.686
Oh, I see!

00:10:44.895 --> 00:10:48.065
He cannot afford to try and dodge the
blows because of their incredible speed!

00:10:48.523 --> 00:10:49.316
No...

00:10:49.566 --> 00:10:50.776
With Guts' skill...

00:10:50.901 --> 00:10:53.278
...he should be able to evade it and
then rush forward with his sword drawn.

00:10:54.029 --> 00:10:56.698
There's no need for him to
damage his sword like that...

00:11:03.288 --> 00:11:04.706
He's protecting me...

00:11:13.840 --> 00:11:14.841
He's injured...

00:11:16.343 --> 00:11:18.679
The arrow wound
I inflicted upon you when...

00:11:18.804 --> 00:11:21.723
...you were trying to protect that
woman, it seems to be bothering you!

00:11:23.058 --> 00:11:24.351
Quit your dawdling!

00:11:24.476 --> 00:11:25.602
He's been injured!

00:11:25.811 --> 00:11:27.479
Finish him off quickly!

00:11:28.355 --> 00:11:29.106
Hey!

00:11:30.190 --> 00:11:32.067
I'll clear the way for you...

00:11:32.359 --> 00:11:35.570
...and then you sprint for the woods.

00:11:36.113 --> 00:11:36.613
But...

00:11:45.330 --> 00:11:45.997
What the...

00:12:12.399 --> 00:12:14.151
S-Samson...

00:12:14.526 --> 00:12:15.360
Now!

00:12:15.527 --> 00:12:16.403
Get away from here!

00:12:16.903 --> 00:12:18.280
Get your ass moving!

00:12:18.405 --> 00:12:19.239
Run!

00:12:19.656 --> 00:12:20.240
But...

00:12:20.532 --> 00:12:21.533
What are you doing?

00:12:21.742 --> 00:12:22.492
Go right now!

00:12:22.909 --> 00:12:23.994
No way...

00:12:24.411 --> 00:12:25.662
I just can't...

00:12:27.289 --> 00:12:28.665
I won't leave without you!

00:12:30.792 --> 00:12:31.668
Shoot!

00:12:32.002 --> 00:12:33.879
Aim for the woman and kill her off!

00:12:41.803 --> 00:12:42.679
Foolish!

00:12:43.180 --> 00:12:47.184
You repeatedly get wounded
on behalf of a mere woman.

00:12:47.809 --> 00:12:50.270
How stupid you are!

00:12:53.815 --> 00:12:54.816
Why?

00:12:55.192 --> 00:12:56.818
Don't mistake my meaning...

00:12:58.028 --> 00:13:01.698
A sickly person is of no use
here, so I want you to get lost.

00:13:02.449 --> 00:13:04.701
It's not my nature to evade the enemy.

00:13:05.577 --> 00:13:10.207
Besides, I've got to get
even with that sniveling bastard.

00:13:11.833 --> 00:13:18.298
As you said, maybe I'm
content just wielding my sword...

00:13:19.674 --> 00:13:21.968
But you're different, right?

00:13:24.054 --> 00:13:27.307
Do you want to die in a place like this?

00:13:28.600 --> 00:13:32.187
Do you want to die a
meaningless death in this little skirmish?

00:13:33.104 --> 00:13:36.733
Has the wish you hold in your
heart rotted away that much?

00:13:38.485 --> 00:13:41.738
A sword is to be put into a sheath.

00:13:43.490 --> 00:13:46.868
Go back to the
sheath your master holds.

00:13:49.079 --> 00:13:51.122
Go back to Griffith.

00:14:03.468 --> 00:14:06.638
Go back to the
sheath your master holds.

00:14:07.639 --> 00:14:09.850
Go back to Griffith.

00:14:39.671 --> 00:14:40.922
Hurry up!

00:14:41.047 --> 00:14:41.548
Run!

00:14:42.924 --> 00:14:43.675
Go!

00:14:43.884 --> 00:14:45.010
Get out of here!

00:14:48.805 --> 00:14:51.057
I promise to return with our comrades!

00:14:51.182 --> 00:14:52.517
Don't die until then!

00:14:57.314 --> 00:14:58.690
Don't let her get away!

00:14:58.815 --> 00:15:00.442
Get her and kill her off!

00:15:02.652 --> 00:15:06.197
You shouldn't go chasing around
women until after you get your work done...

00:15:06.448 --> 00:15:07.908
...you scheming cowards!

00:15:08.074 --> 00:15:09.659
You bastard!

00:15:18.585 --> 00:15:20.170
W-What a man!

00:15:20.337 --> 00:15:23.340
He beats armored men as if
they were cherries to be picked.

00:15:23.465 --> 00:15:26.843
It's unbelievable, but a man
drops every time he swings his sword!

00:15:27.344 --> 00:15:30.472
I didn't know that such a man
existed among the enemy lines.

00:15:32.849 --> 00:15:36.686
My sword is blunt,
the blade has gotten dull.

00:15:37.228 --> 00:15:41.441
However, it's three times as thick
and three times as heavy as any other.

00:15:42.317 --> 00:15:45.320
Just hope you die when I hit
you, or you'll be in lots of pain.

00:15:47.238 --> 00:15:49.074
You son of a bitch!

00:15:49.616 --> 00:15:50.367
Look here!

00:15:50.867 --> 00:15:52.702
You all stop dawdling right now!

00:15:52.953 --> 00:15:56.247
Though he is skilled, the
enemy is only one wounded man!

00:15:56.706 --> 00:15:59.250
He won't come to
much if we surround him!

00:15:59.960 --> 00:16:01.503
We number one hundred men!

00:16:01.628 --> 00:16:02.504
Get him!

00:16:02.963 --> 00:16:04.506
Don't talk nonsense.

00:16:04.714 --> 00:16:07.592
Is there anyone who wants
to take revenge for Samson?

00:16:08.009 --> 00:16:09.344
No one wants to.

00:16:09.469 --> 00:16:12.389
Are you all really
proud knights of Chuder?

00:16:12.514 --> 00:16:14.265
Actually, us over here are mercenaries.

00:16:17.519 --> 00:16:21.731
I will pay triple the reward I
promised, if someone beheads him...

00:16:22.399 --> 00:16:25.986
No wait, I'll even
increase the amount by five...

00:16:27.404 --> 00:16:31.032
And, I'll guarantee your
promotion to battalion commander!

00:16:31.282 --> 00:16:33.118
F-Five times the reward...

00:16:33.284 --> 00:16:34.411
What should we do?

00:16:34.786 --> 00:16:36.913
Naturally, we've got to give it a shot.

00:16:37.497 --> 00:16:40.667
It looks like he can't move
around too much with that wound.

00:16:40.792 --> 00:16:43.294
It'll be okay if we get a group
of five men or so to challenge him.

00:16:45.046 --> 00:16:47.132
What are you bitching about?

00:16:47.674 --> 00:16:48.925
I'm leaving then.

00:16:50.760 --> 00:16:53.805
Yeah, mercenaries have to
be like this, they never learn.

00:16:54.055 --> 00:16:54.806
Do they?

00:17:14.284 --> 00:17:14.909
Pursuers?

00:17:15.910 --> 00:17:16.661
Four...

00:17:17.037 --> 00:17:18.538
No, there are five...

00:17:38.016 --> 00:17:38.892
Dig!

00:17:47.442 --> 00:17:48.526
Pull yourself together!

00:17:48.651 --> 00:17:50.445
Dammit, that bitch...

00:17:50.570 --> 00:17:52.072
Get her!

00:18:11.174 --> 00:18:12.467
What are you doing?

00:18:12.592 --> 00:18:14.177
Kill him at once!

00:18:25.980 --> 00:18:26.689
We did it!

00:18:32.320 --> 00:18:33.071
Good!

00:18:33.196 --> 00:18:35.865
We've crippled his left hand now!

00:18:36.866 --> 00:18:41.496
He won't be able to wield
his huge sword so easily.

00:18:41.830 --> 00:18:42.997
Beat him!

00:18:47.377 --> 00:18:49.629
Now it's getting interesting.

00:19:23.663 --> 00:19:25.039
This is the end...

00:19:25.415 --> 00:19:26.916
I can't run anymore...

00:19:48.771 --> 00:19:50.940
Oopsie, I bet you'd like
to get your hands on that.

00:19:51.065 --> 00:19:54.944
You put us through a lot of trouble, girl.

00:19:58.948 --> 00:20:02.577
We can put you out
of your misery soon, but...

00:20:03.578 --> 00:20:08.082
A whole bunch of my
comrades were killed by you, so...

00:20:08.333 --> 00:20:12.086
Before killing you off, I've
got to thank you for that.

00:20:27.435 --> 00:20:29.979
Don't glower at me like that.

00:20:30.188 --> 00:20:35.610
I'm offering you all the fun you want
right before setting out for the afterlife.

00:20:36.069 --> 00:20:38.821
You should show me some gratitude.

00:20:42.200 --> 00:20:43.493
Well, well...

00:20:55.880 --> 00:20:58.341
What's wrong, are you embarrassed?

00:20:58.758 --> 00:21:01.886
I don't care if you command
a thousand men in battle or not.

00:21:02.345 --> 00:21:05.765
But now, look at you, you
don't seem to be resisting me at all.

00:21:12.772 --> 00:21:15.483
I'm unable to push this bastard aside...

00:21:16.276 --> 00:21:17.235
My...

00:21:17.360 --> 00:21:19.737
My arm is so powerless...

00:22:02.947 --> 00:22:05.074
<i>Looking back, the morning comes.</i>

00:22:05.199 --> 00:22:08.703
<i>Don't find your face in your glass.</i>

00:22:09.954 --> 00:22:12.790
<i>Take the moonlight by the tail.</i>

00:22:12.832 --> 00:22:15.710
<i>It's a rainy sight that you're shading.</i>

00:22:17.462 --> 00:22:18.963
<i>What is that?</i>

00:22:19.088 --> 00:22:20.214
<i>It's just the same.</i>

00:22:20.340 --> 00:22:23.426
<i>What is trying on your crown?</i>

00:22:24.719 --> 00:22:27.597
<i>I'm spending my
glass and walking back.</i>

00:22:27.722 --> 00:22:30.933
<i>So wear my glass, you're fading.</i>

00:22:31.225 --> 00:22:34.562
<i>I'm waiting so long.</i>

00:22:34.979 --> 00:22:37.940
<i>I'm waiting so long.</i>

00:22:38.608 --> 00:22:41.611
<i>I'm waiting so long.</i>

00:22:42.487 --> 00:22:45.323
<i>I'm waiting...</i>

00:23:06.886 --> 00:23:08.346
Next Episode

00:23:08.346 --> 00:23:08.888
Everyone has a flame burning in their heart,
which cannot be extinguished. Next Episode

00:23:08.888 --> 00:23:14.769
Everyone has a flame burning in their
heart, which cannot be extinguished.

00:23:15.770 --> 00:23:19.148
In the flicker of the flame,
there is a brilliance to be found.

00:23:19.482 --> 00:23:23.903
It burns on ambition, it warms the
heart, and it reduces feelings to ashes.

00:23:24.654 --> 00:23:27.156
The question arises...

00:23:27.657 --> 00:23:31.244
Will the flame of fate ever be
extinguished as long as man lives?

00:23:33.913 --> 00:23:36.916
Bonfire of Dreams

00:23:37.305 --> 00:24:37.292
